We found a small leak in ft_split:
void	free_all(char **new, int w)
{
	while (w > 0)
		free(new[w--]);
},
this skips index 0 while freeing the array (fix: change > to >=).
We also found a weird issue with big negative numbers not being sorted, we identified that it starts happening once the biggest difference between values is > INT_MAX, it seems to break the insertion logic.
Also, 01 is a valid number in C, no need to throw an error on that.
Otherwise, the code looks good and works well, did not find any issues besides the ones above, and the algorithm is well understood & explained.
Good luck with fixing!

